news.title: Ludhiana’s Smart City mission in further drag
news.para: It has been nine long years since the Smart City mission was launched, and Ludhiana was among the first 20 cities selected for this central programme.

news.title: Residents of Haware Citi in Thane up in arms against upcoming ready mix plants
news.para: Hyderabad-based Megha Engineering and Infrastructure Ltd is setting up two ready-mix cement (RMC) plants just a few hundred metres from their residential complex.

news.title: Land record management digitised in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Earlier the process was cumbersome for the buyer and seller, and required a compulsory visit to the taluk office for patta transfer, requesting measurement of land and for all land record based services.

news.title: Mumbai: About 1,700 shanties in Bandra West razed for slum rehabilitation project
news.para: The multi-storied slum pocket, called Shastri Nagar, had touched the boundary of platform 1 of Bandra station for the past several decades.

news.title: Paradigm Realty to redevelop 11 societies in Mumbai's Bandra, Kandivali
news.para: These projects in Bandra’s Pali Hill and Carter Road areas, and Kandivali’s Mahavir Nagar, are estimated to have development potential of over 2.8 million sq ft.

news.title: Haryana CM distributes plot allotment letters to over 15,000 beneficiaries
news.para: At the event held at Maharshi Dayanand University in Rohtak, the chief minister handed out plot allotment letters to the beneficiaries on the spot, the release said.

news.title: YEIDA cancels allotment of plots to Sunworld Infrastructure & Supertech Township
news.para: Also, the authority, which functions under the Uttar Pradesh government, has given time till August 31 to developer ATS Realty and Greenbay Infrastructure till July 31 to clear their dues.

news.title: US government awards $85 million to ease affordable housing development
news.para: A chronic shortage of housing is continuing to drive up rentals and lingering consumer price inflation, contributing to a delay in Federal Reserve interest rate cuts.

news.title: Shimao Group's liquidation petition adjourned by Hong Kong court
news.para: The adjournment was made by a Hong Kong court following a consensual application for such a move by Shimao and the petitioner - state-owned lender China Construction Bank (Asia) - the filing to the Hong Kong Stock Exchange said.

news.title: Beijing lowers minimum down payment ratio for home buyers
news.para: The moves, announced in a local government statement, come after the central bank issued new guidelines on reducing minimum mortgage rates and down-payments last month, which sparked dozens of cities to relax property policies.

news.title: KKR acquires $2.1 billion portfolio of real estate assets from Quarterra
news.para: The portfolio includes 5,200 units across California, Washington, Florida, Texas, Georgia, North Carolina, Colorado and New Jersey, the global commercial property industry, in particular offices, is still in the grip of its biggest slump since the 2007-9 financial crisis.

news.title: Srinagar: Homes start to develop cracks due to land subsidence in Rainawari
news.para: The cracks widened with each passing day. We approached the administration, which asked us to vacate the houses," local resident Manzoor Ahmed said.

news.title: Gross leasing of office space up 8% in Apr-Jun in top six cities: Colliers
news.para: Real estate consultant Colliers India said that gross absorption or leasing does not include lease renewals, pre-commitments and deals where only a letter of Intent has been signed.

news.title: ESZ committee directs Jaipur civic body to raze hotel property on Nahargarh land
news.para: The decision was taken after the standing committee of the National Board for Wildlife (NBWL) refused to grant wildlife clearance to the hotel project at a meeting held on Feb 22 earlier this year.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to extend OTS tax facility to Rs 5 lakh khata-less properties
news.para: According to BBMP officials, the March OTS rollout was delayed because of the Lok Sabha elections. Officials hope to generate Rs 800 crore to Rs 1,000 crore a year through the scheme.

news.title: PMAY-Urban's second phase to build one crore houses to be launched soon
news.para: The Union Cabinet of Modi 3.0 government, in its first meeting held on June 10 under the chairmanship of Prime Minister Narendra Modi, approved government assistance for the construction of three crore houses under the PMAY.

news.title: Noida: A new property registry office to be set up in Dadri
news.para: Residents have raised questions over the govt’s decision, asking why they must travel all the way to Dadri to get their properties registered when a similar office could be set up closer home.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves extension of Noida metro's aqua line
news.para: The proposed metro extension is designed to address the growing demand for efficient and reliable public transportation. The project will enhance connectivity, the NMRC said.

news.title: Karnataka government invites applications for K-RERA’s new chairperson post
news.para: Home buyers are urging the state government to appoint a qualified and knowledgeable individual with integrity for the K-RERA Chairperson position.

news.title: UltraTech Cement offers to acquire 25% of UAE’s RAKWCT
news.para: This offer was revised to 12.50 crore shares of RAKWCT representing 25 per cent of the share capital of RAKWCT, UltraTech Cement said in a regulatory filing on Tuesday.
